# NeonMacro Project Map

- Purpose: Windows CustomTkinter desktop tool for profile-based key spamming to target apps via Win32 PostMessage.
- App entry: src/neonmacro/app.py (single-instance guard, logging setup, launches MainWindow).
- Main feature hub: src/neonmacro/ui/main_window.py (profile CRUD, hotkeys, engine state, options, overlay visibility logic).
- Core runtime pieces: src/neonmacro/core/spam_engine.py (send loop), src/neonmacro/core/hotkeys.py (global/profile hotkeys), src/neonmacro/core/config.py (JSON load/save), src/neonmacro/core/startup.py (Windows Run-key startup registration).
- Overlay + targeting: src/neonmacro/core/overlay.py, src/neonmacro/ui/overlay_controller.py, src/neonmacro/targeting/window_targeting.py.
- Tray integration: src/neonmacro/ui/system_tray.py (system tray icon/menu), src/neonmacro/ui/main_window.py (minimize-to-tray and restore wiring).

# Maintenance Rule

Always update this file (`.cursor/rules/project-map.mdc`) whenever project changes affect feature routing context, including:

- New/renamed/removed entry points.
- New/renamed/removed core feature modules.
- Significant ownership shifts (feature logic moved to different files).
- New subsystems that should be part of the short project map.
